      "parent_index": null,
      "last_updated": "2026-05-20T10:35:55.643356",
      "order": 2,
      "alignment": "left",
      "body": "Fisher's classic Iris dataset \u2014 **150 flowers** across three varieties\n(*Setosa*, *Versicolor*, *Virginica*). This dashboard surfaces the\ncohort-level structure: cards summarise the four measurement columns\nwith min/median/max strips, the scatter and box plots show species\nseparability on sepal dimensions, and the histogram strip exposes\ndistribution overlap. Use the left filters to narrow down by\nvariety or sepal length and watch every tile re-compute.\n",
      "wf_tag": "python/iris_workflow"
    },
